Meningitis - India (Bihar): RFI 20001209.2162
Date: 12 Dec 2000 11:08:30
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Times of India [edited
<http://www.timesofindia.com/today/12hlth16.htm>

65 Die of Meningitis in Nawada
------------------------------
With 4 more deaths, meningitis has so far claimed 65 lives in Kauakaul and
Rajaul blocks in Bihar's Nawada district in the last month, official
sources said.
The civil surgeon in-charge of Nawada, Sheo Dayal Das, said here on Monday
that 4 members of a family died of the deadly disease at Dudhiyatand
village under Kauakal block in the district in Nawada on Sunday evening [10
Dec 2000. Also afflicted were 2 others hospitalized at Sadar hospital here.
